Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "shvatite" in different forms and positions:

1. *Shvatite* ozbiljno situaciju u kojoj se nalazimo. (Take seriously the situation we are in.)
2. Molim vas da *shvatite* da je ovo važno pitanje. (Please understand that this is an important issue.)
3. Ako *shvatite* da ste pogrešili, ispravite to odmah. (If you realize that you have made a mistake, correct it immediately.)
4. Nisam siguran da *shvatam* šta želite da kažete. (I'm not sure I understand what you're trying to say.)
5. Da bi uspeli, moramo *shvatiti* šta su naši ciljevi. (In order to succeed, we must understand what our goals are.)
6. Nadam se da ćeš *shvatiti* koliko mi je stalo do tebe. (I hope you'll understand how much I care about you.)
7. *Shvatićeš* tek kad budeš u njihovoj koži. (You'll only understand when you're in their shoes.)
8. Ako *ne shvatite* ozbiljno situaciju, mogli bismo se naći u velikom problemu. (If you don't take the situation seriously, we could be in big trouble.)

I hope these examples help!